dc_description_s: AMS 1. North Decimal Degree 24.850000. South Decimal Degree 24.800000. East Decimal Degree 121.000000. West Decimal Degree 120.916667. Alternate title: Shinchiku. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals. Place names are transcribed according to the Modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to Hsin-chu [Hsinchu]. Compiled from aerial photography dated October 1943, February 1944, and September 1944, by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:50,000, A.M.S., Sheets 2221-I and 2221-II, 1944; Town Plan of Shinchiku 1:7,400 approx., OSS, No. 3356, 1944; Formosa 1:25,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2221-II NE, 1944. Additional Information from intelligence data.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
